The paper discusses a learning approach for controlling motor primitives in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves prioritizing sub-tasks, which can be achieved through machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of dominance structures to resolve conflicts between sub-tasks is a key aspect of the approach, which relates to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the evaluation of the approach involves a task that requires visual perception, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
